<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1246,2033]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1446,1472]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name comes from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[823,926,1447,1472]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Lysiteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distortus">
<emphasis box="[823,926,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">distortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning twisted and referring to the shape of the base of the embolus, adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1246,2033]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1526,1552]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang, Zhu &amp; Tso, 2006" authorityName="Zhang, Zhu &amp; Tso" authorityYear="2006" box="[627,1050,1526,1552]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Lysiteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torsivus">
<emphasis box="[627,751,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. torsivus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang" box="[758,1050,1526,1552]" pageId="16" pageNumber="41" refString="Zhang, J. X., Zhu, M. S. &amp; Tso, I. M. (2006) Four new crab spiders from Taiwan (Araneae, Thomisidae). Journal of Arachnology, 34, 77 - 86." type="journal article" year="2006">
Zhang, Zhu &amp; Tso, 
<number box="[991,1050,1526,1552]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1066,1156,1526,1552]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 a – e" captionStartId="34.[151,269,1257,1281]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,189,1229]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,189,1231]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 18 a – e. Lysiteles torsivus Zhang, Zhu &amp; Tso, 2006. a Male, habitus; b – e Left palp (b prolateral, c – d ventral, e retrolateral view). Scale bars: a = 1; b – e = 0.1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181560/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Figs 
<number box="[1126,1156,1526,1552]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) in general appearance, but can be separated from the latter by: the embolus much longer and slender, twisted in anticlockwise (thick and twisted in clockwise in 
<taxonomicName box="[480,605,1607,1632]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Lysiteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torsivus">
<emphasis box="[480,605,1607,1632]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. torsivus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); embolus originated at the position of 
<number box="[1072,1087,1606,1632]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="9.0">9</number>
:00 o’clock versus 
<number box="[1311,1340,1606,1632]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="12.0">12</number>
o’clock in 
<taxonomicName box="[181,305,1647,1672]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Lysiteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torsivus">
<emphasis box="[181,305,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. torsivus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; RTA almost as long as VTA in ventral view versus almost two times longer than VTA in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Lysiteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torsivus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. torsivus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1246,2033]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,152,498]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,422,1726,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[439,549,1726,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
): Total length 
<number box="[719,774,1726,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.15">3.15</number>
. Prosoma 
<number box="[898,949,1726,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.55">1.55</number>
long; 
<number box="[1026,1077,1726,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.43">1.43</number>
wide; opisthosoma 
<number box="[1317,1368,1726,1752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.81">1.81</number>
long, 
<number box="[151,202,1766,1792]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.52">1.52</number>
wide. Dorsal shield of prosoma brown, with a large “n”-shaped black marking. Ocular area black, eye sizes and interdistances: ALE 
<number box="[521,575,1807,1833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.2">0.20</number>
, PLE 
<number box="[655,709,1807,1833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.14">0.14</number>
, AME 
<number box="[801,855,1807,1833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.09">0.09</number>
, PME 
<number box="[943,997,1807,1833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.06">0.06</number>
, AME-AME 
<number box="[1164,1218,1807,1833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, AME-ALE 
<number box="[1377,1431,1807,1833]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.18">0.18</number>
, PME-PME 
<number box="[289,343,1847,1873]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.27">0.27</number>
, PME-PLE 
<number box="[486,541,1847,1873]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.32">0.32</number>
; MOA 
<number box="[629,680,1847,1873]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.29">0.29</number>
long, front width 
<number box="[895,949,1847,1873]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.38">0.38</number>
, back width 
<number box="[1099,1154,1847,1873]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.4">0.40</number>
. Sternum yellow, cordiform. Chelicerae, labium and gnathocoxae blackish brown. Legs yellow, distal parts of tarsi blackish brown. Leg measurements: I: 
<number box="[412,464,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="5.6">5.60</number>
(
<number box="[480,535,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.7">1.70</number>
, 
<number box="[547,601,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.8">1.80</number>
, 
<number box="[613,667,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.2">1.20</number>
, 
<number box="[679,735,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.9">0.90</number>
), II: 6.00 (
<number box="[857,912,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.8">1.80</number>
, 
<number box="[924,978,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.9">1.90</number>
, 
<number box="[990,1044,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.3">1.30</number>
, 1.00), III: 4.00 (
<number box="[1244,1299,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.3">1.30</number>
, 
<number box="[1311,1365,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.4">1.40</number>
, 
<number box="[1377,1431,1927,1953]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.7">0.70</number>
, 
<number box="[151,207,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.6">0.60</number>
), IV: 
<number box="[273,324,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.3">4.30</number>
(
<number box="[342,397,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.4">1.40</number>
, 
<number box="[410,464,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.5">1.50</number>
, 
<number box="[478,532,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.8">0.80</number>
, 
<number box="[545,601,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="0.6">0.60</number>
); formula 2, 1, 4, 3. Legs with short spines, femora I with 
<number box="[1300,1315,1967,1993]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
prolateral spines, femora I–IV with 
<number box="[459,474,2007,2033]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
dorsal spines, tibiae and metatarsi I, II with 
<number box="[1014,1029,2007,2033]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of ventral spines, tibiae and metatarsi III, IV with 
<number box="[422,436,152,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of ventral spines. Opisthosoma dorsum brown; anteriorly with 
<number box="[1270,1285,152,178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
small white medial spots and a pair of longitudinal grayish black bilateral markings; posteriorly with 
<number box="[1199,1214,192,218]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of transverse black stripes; laterally with some black lines; venter grayish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[198,254,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Palp</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[270,399,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 a – e" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1667,1691]" captionTargetBox="[229,1360,597,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[226,1360,597,1641]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 8 a – e. Lysiteles distortus sp. nov. a Male, habitus; b – e Left palp (b prolateral, c – d ventral, d retrolateral view). Scale bars: a = 1; b – e = 0.1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181550/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Figs 
<number box="[330,344,272,298]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="8.0">8</number>
b–e
</figureCitation>
). VTA apically curved; RTA stout with many black denticles, each denticle with a short hair, RTA with 
<number box="[331,345,312,338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2.0">2</number>
sharp apophyses; cymbium wide; embolus slender, the base twisted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,498]" box="[198,423,351,378]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,299,351,377]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Female:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,391,417]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Variation.</emphasis>
Total length: males 
<number box="[577,694,392,418]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2.9" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.5">2.50–3.30</number>
(n = 
<number box="[768,785,392,418]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="5.0">5</number>
). Two specimens with three pairs of black transverse stripes on opisthosoma dorsum posteriorly.
</paragraph>
